        # Project manifest\n├── package-lock.json             # Locked dependencies\n├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript configuration\n├── vitest.config.ts              # Vitest test runner config\n├── .eslintrc.cjs                 # ESLint configuration\n├── .gitignore                    # Git ignore rules\n├── TASK.md                       # Task description and constraints\n└── (other generated files)\n```\n\n---\n\n### Source Files Summary\n\n#### **src/server.ts** (Express Application)\n- Sets up Express.js API server\n- 6 endpoints:\n  - `GET /invoices` - List invoices by date range\n  - `GET /invoices/:id` - Get single invoice with line items\n  - `POST /invoices` - Create new invoice\n  - `GET /reports/monthly` - Monthly revenue report\n  - `GET /reports/customer/:id` - Customer report\n- Input validation and error handling\n\n#### **src/models/invoice.ts** (TypeScript Interfaces)\n- `LineItem` - Individual line items on invoices\n- `Invoice` - Invoice record with customer, dates, totals, status\n- `InvoiceCreateInput` - Input schema for creating invoices\n- `InvoiceSummary` - Monthly summary data\n- `CustomerReport` - Customer financial metrics\n\n#### **src/db/connection.ts** (SQLite Setup)\n- Creates in-memory or file-based SQLite database\n- Configures WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) pragma\n- Initializes two tables:\n  - `invoices` - Main invoice records\n  - `line_items` - Line items for each invoice (foreign key relation)\n\n#### **src/db/queries.ts** (Database Layer)\n- `getInvoicesByDateRange()` - Retrieves invoices within date range\n- `getInvoiceById()` - Fetches single invoice with associated line items\n- `createInvoice()` - Inserts invoice and associated line items\n- `getInvoicesByCustomer()` - Lists all invoices for a customer\n\n#### **src/services/billing.ts** (Business Logic - POTENTIALLY BUGGY)\n- `calculateInvoiceTotal()` - **BUG POTENTIAL**: Calculates total using formula: `subtotal * (1 - discount) * (1 + tax)`\n  - Line 18: `const total = discounted + subtotal * taxRate;` - This looks incorrect!\n  - Should apply tax to the discounted amount, not the original subtotal\n- `applyDiscount()` - Applies percentage discount to subtotal\n- `calculateSubtotal()` - Sums line item costs (quantity × unit_price)\n- `generateInvoice()` - Creates invoice with calculated totals\n\n#### **src/services/reporting.ts** (Reporting Engine)\n- `getMonthlyReport()` - Groups invoices by month, counts and sums revenue\n- `getCustomerReport()` - Calculates invoice count, total spent, average invoice\n- `getRevenueByPeriod()` - Sums revenue within date range\n\n#### **src/utils/dates.ts** (Date Utilities)\n- `formatDate()` - Converts Date to ISO string (YYYY-MM-DD) using UTC\n- `parseDate()` - Parses ISO string to Date in UTC\n- `getMonthRange()` - Gets first/last dates of a month\n- `isDateInRange()` - Checks if date falls within range\n\n#### **src/utils/format.ts** (Formatting Utilities)\n- `formatCurrency()` - Formats number as currency ($X,XXX.XX)\n- `formatPercentage()` - Formats decimal rate as percentage\n- `calculateTax()` - **KNOWN BUG** (legacy, unused): Multiplies by rate*100 instead of just rate\n\n---\n\n### Test Files Summary\n\n#### **tests/invoices.test.ts** (23 Tests)\n- **Invoice CRUD (8 tests):**\n  - Create/retrieve invoices\n  - Line items association\n  - Customer filtering\n  - Sorting by date\n  - Status storage\n\n- **Billing Calculations (8 tests):**\n  - Total calculation with/without discount\n  - Discount application\n  - Zero-rate handling\n  - Invoice generation with line items\n  - Multiple items with discount\n\n- **Date Range Queries (7 tests):**\n  - Range retrieval\n  - Boundary inclusion\n  - Month spanning\n  - Full year ranges\n\n#### **tests/regression.test.ts** (10 Tests)\n- Specific bug regression tests\n- Tests discount calculations (15%, 20%)\n- Month boundary assignments\n- Date range end-date inclusion\n- Large invoice precision\n- Single-day ranges\n- 100% discount edge case\n\n#### **tests/diff-size.test.ts** (1 Test)\n- **Constraint test**: Enforces max 20 lines of changes in src/\n- Counts added (+) and removed (-) lines from git diff\n\n---\n\n### Key Observations & Potential Bugs\n\n1. **Critical Bug in `calculateInvoiceTotal()` (src/services/billing.ts, line 18):**\n   - Current: `const total = discounted + subtotal * taxRate;`\n   - Problem: Tax is applied to original subtotal, not discounted amount\n   - Expected: Tax should be applied to the discounted subtotal\n   - Should be: `const total = discounted * (1 + taxRate);`\n   - This would explain why several billing tests might fail\n\n2. **Date Range Query (src/db/queries.ts, line 14):**\n   - Uses `date < ?` (exclusive) instead of `date <= ?` (inclusive)\n   - Tests expect inclusive end date\n   - Needs fixing to: `WHERE date >= ? AND date <= ?`\n\n3. **Legacy bug in format.ts** (unused, won't break tests):\n   - `calculateTax()` multiplies by `rate * 100` instead of just `rate`\n   - Not used in active code path\n\n4. **Timezone handling:**\n   - Tests force `TZ=America/New_York` to expose timezone bugs\n   - Code uses UTC methods throughout (getUTC* methods)\n   - Appears correctly implemented\n\n---\n\n### Dependencies\n\n**Runtime:**\n- `better-sqlite3@^11.0.0` - SQLite database\n- `express@^4.21.0` - Web framework\n\n**Dev Tools:**\n- `typescript@^5.4.0` - Type checker and compiler\n- `vitest@^2.0.0` - Test runner\n- `eslint@^8.56.0` - Linter\n- `supertest@^7.0.0` - HTTP assertions for testing\n- Type definitions for all major dependencies\n\n---\n\n### Build & Test Commands\n\n```bash\nnpm install       # Install dependencies\nnpm test          # Run all tests (expected: 4 failing out of 30 visible + 10 hidden)\nnpm run build     # TypeScript compilation to dist/\nnpm run lint      # ESLint check\n```\n\n---\n\n### Constraints for Bug Fix\n\n- Maximum 20 lines changed in `src/` (added + removed lines)\n- Must not modify test files\n- All 30 visible tests + 10 hidd